2) What CO₂ is in the loop

You were close, but here’s the precise version:
	•	O₂ (oxygen) → carried to tissues → used in mitochondria to make ATP
	•	This produces CO₂ as a waste product of metabolism
	•	CO₂ is then:
	•	partly dissolved
	•	partly bound to hemoglobin
	•	mostly carried as bicarbonate (HCO₃⁻)

Then you exhale it.

